##There are more and more "dancing girls" in the shelter hospital, but there is still a shortage of psychologists

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Zhao Siwei, a reporter for the paper, in Wuhan

On the afternoon of February 6, a female nurse at the Union Medical College Hospital whispered a greeting of the new arrival at Kong Hon's Shelter Hospital. Source:@wuhan posted 01:17

"We understand that you may feel uncomfortable or even nervous or anxious in a new environment. We hope that you can relax your body and calm your mind together with the rhythm of the music. " In the Kong Hon Shelter Hospital in Wuhan, Hubei Province, a female nurse from the Wuhan Union Hospital said softly.

Hu deying, deputy director of the Wuhan Union Hospital and head of the psychological counseling team at the Shelter Hospital, said that in order to ease the tension of patients arriving at the Shelter Hospital for the first time, the Concorde Hospital took over the Jianghan shelter hospital, first introduced in the shelter hospital psychological counseling mechanism, by the Union Hospital Psychological Advisory Expert Group stationed.

The paper has learned that the medical teams at the two shelter hospitals in Wuchang and Kong Hon, which have treated more than 2,000 patients with NCP, have produced a good report card on how to calm patients'emotions and conduct psychological counseling.

Behind the report card, there are measures such as improving the patient's convalescent environment, opening a radio station to answer questions, popularizing science, compiling and printing a psychological manual to guide self-guidance, etc. , explain the significance of the shelter and the efforts of the doctors and nurses. There are more and more "dancing girls" and "gymnastics patients" in the square cabin hospital of Wuhan.

However, it can not be ignored that there are still a large number of patients and a small number of professional psychologists.
Xiao Jinsong, senior psychological consultant of Zhongnan Hospital of Wuhan University and President of Hubei Association of Psychological Consultants, told The Paper on February 10 that it is risky behavior for social psychological counseling forces to enter the shelter for psychological counseling, at present, it is a feasible measure for the first-line medical staff to provide psychological comfort and the patients to receive decompression therapy remotely.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Zhao Siweitu, a reporter from the paper, at Kong Hon's Shelter Hospital, which has treated nearly 1,600 patients with new coronary pneumonia

The number of patients, the number of professional psychologists

On the evening of February 5, the Kong Hon and Wuchang's shelter hospitals received the first batch of new mild cases of pneumonia.

Since then, there have been patients because of service facilities, medical care configuration and other issues of discontent, and even patients due to kick over trash cans, and other patients late at night quarrel with the situation.

Zhang Chun, phd, director of the Psychological Crisis Intervention Centre in Nanjing, explained to thepaper.cn that people's fear of the unknown is called "primitive fear" , unfamiliar environment, enclosed space and the threat of "death" , can Affect a person's mood. This kind of emotion affects each other, the energy accumulates, can appear anxious, anxious, the mood reaction of petulance, light show discontented, heavy appear destroy and aggressive behavior.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Outside Wuchang's shelter hospital, Zhao Siwei, reporter, thepaper.cn

When people's activity scope is small, social interaction is few, self-evaluation is low, and live in a claustrophobic and narrow space continuously, individual's destructive behavior is extremely easy to appear. From the point of view of psychology, the emotion is the overflow effect of the pressure, and the pressure is the internal motive force of the emotion. If the individual mood can not find the target of attack, there will appear the compensatory behavior in the sense of psychology, which is the psychological motive of this kind of "the cabin effect" .

Xiao Jinsong, senior psychological consultant of Zhongnan Hospital of Wuhan University and President of Hubei Psychological Consultant Association, and his team have been working together since the day of the "city closure" in Wuhan, has Been using professional expertise to provide psychological support to citizens and health care.

He believes that the symptoms of patients in the shelter hospitals are relatively mild. In addition to problems in professional medical care, they also face problems in daily life, such as indoor temperature and food quality, "It's actually the psychological management behind the life management of logistics, which requires psychological intervention. "

However, this kind of psychological intervention is different from the situation of psychological rescue in disaster areas such as earthquake before. During the hospitalization of patients, social psychological counselors enter the hospital. First, they do not have this qualification; second, they will also plunge them into a dangerous situation, because they don't have any professional training.

Xiao Jinsong believes that in the current unbalanced situation of more patients and fewer professional psychologists, after excluding the power of social psychological consultation, at present, the first-line medical and nursing staff's physical and psychological comfort and the patients'long-distance decompression become more feasible measures.

He explained that the medical staff who entered the shelter had studied psychology in school, but most had not done so after graduation. By the professional team to the medical staff to do simple training, let them become a non-professional psychological workers, can do some psychological comfort work. "If you have a professional team to train, train; if you don't, you can turn to social forces for training. "

After several days of psychological counseling for patients with NCP and medical care, Xiao's team compiled the "manual of psychological intervention for pneumonia with COVID-19 infection" .

The manual details psychological interventions and stress relief measures for groups of patients who have been diagnosed, suspected patients, medical care and related personnel, those in close contact with patients, and those who have fever but do not wish to see a doctor openly.

According to the manual, the psychological symptoms of patients diagnosed and treated in isolation are numbness, anger, fear, depression, loneliness, or fear of the disease and not cooperate, abandon treatment.

In this case, we should take according to the patient can accept the degree, objective and honest account of the disease and the outside epidemic situation, so that patients do know; Actively encourage patients to cooperate with treatment, help reflect the problem, try to help improve the patient's medical environment and other measures.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A patient holds a psychological manual entitled "walking into a shelter" at a shelter hospital in Wuchang. Photo provided by interviewee

Compiling and printing psychological manual, the medical treatment uses the action to ease the patient's mood

Wuchang's shelter hospital is one of the first of three to open, with a planned capacity of 800 beds. Since the first batch of patients were admitted on the evening of February 5,467 patients with mild cases of new pneumonia had been admitted as of 8 am on February 10.

Wan Jun, deputy director of the People's Hospital of Wuhan University and head of Wuchang's shelter hospital, told The Paper news on February 10 that in response to the psychological problems reflected by the patients, on the one hand, the dynamic improvement of the patients'convalescent environment, raise the standard of heating and food for patients. On the other hand, through the establishment of the hospital radio, the compilation of "into the shelter" psychological counseling manual, the establishment of the general branch of the patients and other forms of timely answers to everyone's questions, to avoid emotional panic, psychological counseling.

In addition, the front-line medical staff through their thoughtful service to do "silent" psychological counseling. Wanjun said most of the medical personnel who came to support Wuhan came from other provinces. Many of them came after 90 or 95. Although they had received simple training, they did not have enough knowledge of infectious diseases. Heating, which is comfortable for the patient, is not comfortable for the health care worker in a protective suit. High humidity, high temperature environment, physical exertion is very large, but no one complained tired, some tired up and continue to work.

This very professional, confidence, patience, selflessness to serve the patient spirit is also infected with each patient, patients can also transposition thinking, mood is much better, there are a lot of dance do patients.
The manual, "into the shelter" , referred to by Wan Jun, was written by the Central South University team from Xiangya Second Hospital, which assisted Wuhan and provided medical services at the Shelter Hospital in Wuchang, according to the characteristics of the shelter hospital and the common problems of patients.

According to a review by thepaper.cn, the manual covers everything from how to protect yourself to how to discharge from hospital, from identifying psychological responses to stress, and how to regulate anxiety, to breathing and relaxation, positive cues, and indoor exercise techniques, to try to teach the patient how to build a psychological defense against the disease while he's in the shelter hospital.

Xiangya second hospital officials told The Paper news, after being admitted to the Wuchang Shelter Hospital, see the new crown pneumonia situation is serious, to help patients overcome the heart of panic and anxiety has become an urgent task, the hospital's head of psychiatry was urgently mobilized to prepare the booklet and on the evening of February 7, an additional 1,000 copies were printed and distributed to each patient.

"On the one hand, it helps to relieve patients' stress. On the other hand, it also provides scientific guidance for medical staff to identify and guide patients' psychological problems, so as to ensure scientific, rational and accurate treatment. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Picture shows a radio station set up in Kong Hon's Shelter Hospital

Open the yard broadcast, appear many "dancing girl"

Meanwhile, Kong Hon's Shelter Hospital, which treats nearly 1,600 patients, is also seeking to establish a channel of doctor-patient communication and psychological counseling for patients.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Books for patients by nurses at Kong Hon's Shelter Hospital. Photo by interviewee

Sun Hui, deputy party secretary of the Wuhan Union Hospital and head of the Jianghan Square hospital, told The Paper on the evening of February 9 that efforts have been made to set up a party branch in the hospital, including a branch that includes patients, call on patients with self-help social services; open the Hospital Radio Station, answer questions and Popular Science Knowledge; set up psychological counseling group, to the first-line communication with patients; the establishment of Reading Corner and other initiatives.

"yesterday (the 8th) we addressed the problem of toilet congestion by saying on the radio that we should take care of our environment, and today things will be better, " Sun said.

In the shelter, professional psychological counseling is still in charge of the psychological counseling room teachers, they set up a separate Concorde Hospital Nurses Psychological Counseling Group, there is a patient hotline, opened online counseling. And Consultation on duty, radio duty are psychological counseling volunteers, we are on duty in their own leisure time, volunteers have also taken a psychological consultant certificate. "There are people who are basically not working but are volunteering, who have been there for two days, and there will be a schedule later. "

Hu deying suggested that a certain percentage of volunteer nurses who were psychological counselors could provide physical and psychological care to patients, which is a very complete quality care process.

Radio, as a kind of media, plays a communication role in the shelter.

An internal radio broadcast from Kong Hon's Shelter Hospital showed a female nurse whispering a greeting from the hospital on the afternoon of February 6, according to a video obtained by the paper, "We understand that you may feel uncomfortable or even nervous or anxious in a new and unfamiliar environment. " A light music was played at the end of the broadcast, "I hope you can follow the rhythm of the music and relax your body and calm your mind. "

On the afternoon of February 8th, a soft voice came from the radio station again. "This is Kong Hon's Shelter Hospital Radio Station, and I'm little Jing, a medical officer at Concorde. The Lantern Festival is supposed to be a time for family reunion, but with the new pneumonia raging, we are experiencing an ordinary holiday..."

Hu deying told The Paper news that the broadcasts mainly collected patients'opinions from the nurses in the wards and then answered questions that were of concern to the public on the radio. The radio is now played three times a day, in the morning, in the evening, and light music is played at the end. "We sang 'me and my country' The next day [ after we arrived ] and it was taken seriously and we encouraged patients to put on masks and sing along with us if they could. "

From the effect, now patients are in a much better mood than before, the Popular Online "reading brother" , "dancing sister" is a true portrayal, every day nurses will take time to do some exercise with everyone.
Hu deying told thepaper.cn that the patient in the shelter is a mild case of new coronary pneumonia. He can take care of himself and is relatively depressed during rest and recuperation. Doing exercises and dancing can just ease his mood and has a good response. The netizen is worried of quarrel other person wait for a problem, because frequency also is not very tall, did not receive relevant complain at present.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo courtesy of "dancing girl" interviewees at Kong Hon's Shelter Hospital

On Feb. 9, the paper contacted Ms. He, a patient at Kong Hon's Shelter Hospital who filmed "dancing girl, " who was confirmed to have contracted the new coronavirus on Feb. 5 and was admitted to the Shelter Hospital at Wuhan International Convention and Exhibition Center on Feb. 6. The next day, she filmed the patient dancing.

Compared with some patients appear anxious mood, Ms. He is very optimistic. When she arrived at the shelter, instead of complaining about the limited accommodations, she was more active in her daily life and would join in the dance when she saw patients dancing. She often shares her Three Meals a Day with her friends and shows gratitude to the doctors and nurses who helped her. "I hope everyone will complain less and understand more. "

(interns, Zhang Haorong, Li Xian, Meng Jinjin, Li Ning, Hu Youmei, contributed reporting.)
